        <?php echo $this->stencil->setHeadline('Bell Labs'); ?>
        <p><strong>Bell Laboratories</strong> (also known as <strong>Bell Labs</strong> and formerly known as <strong>AT&amp;T Bell Laboratories</strong> and <strong>Bell Telephone Laboratories</strong>) is the research and development subsidiary of Alcatel-Lucent.</p>
        <p>Bell Laboratories operates its headquarters in Murray Hill, New Jersey, United States, and has research and development facilities throughout the world.</p>
        <p>The historic laboratory originated in the late 19th century as the Volta Laboratory and Bureau created by Alexander Graham Bell.</p>
        <p>Researchers working at Bell Labs are credited with the development of radio astronomy, the transistor, the laser, the charge-coupled device (CCD), information theory, the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('UNIX', 'OS'); ?> operating system, the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C', 'L'); ?> programming language, <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('S', 'L'); ?> programming language and the <?php echo $this->stencil->addLink('C++', 'L'); ?> programming language.</p>
